The paper discusses a software tool for managing changes in object-oriented systems, which is a topic that falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The tool is specifically designed for class diagrams, which are a type of modeling language used in software engineering and programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also mentions the use of Alloy, a formal specification language, which falls under the logic in computer science (cs.LO) sub-category. The tool involves semantic analysis of the diagrams, which could also be related to database systems (cs.DB) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories.
